headline: American Banker Names Fifth Third Commercial Payments Leaders to Annual Most Powerful Women in Banking Lists
summary: CINCINNATI, October 07, 2025--Fifth Third Bank (Nasdaq: FITB) is pleased to announce that Bridgit Chayt, head of commercial payments, has again been named to American Banker’s list of Most Powerful Women in Banking. Jessica Rohrkemper, director commercial payments and treasury management support services, has been named to the publication’s The Most Powerful Women in Banking NEXT list.

headline: Regional Lenders Are Merging to Answer the Challenge From Megabanks
summary: To become a national banking player in the U.S., it seems you must also be a local one.  PNC’s chief executive has ultimately set his sights on roughly doubling its size to $1 trillion in assets—while Colorado-based FirstBank brought in just $27 billion.

headline: Heard on the Street Monday Recap: AMD Circles Back
summary: OpenAI and Advanced Micro Devices struck a multibillion-dollar partnership.  OpenAI committed to buying 6 gigawatts worth of AMD’s chips and will also receive warrants for up to 160 million AMD shares, roughly 10% of the chip company, if OpenAI hits certain deployment milestones.  The deal could add to concerns over the “circularity” of recent AI deals, which blend investments with commercial relationships.
